  <h2>📝 Vocabulary Matching Exercise</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>a. to weaken something or make it less effective — <span class="answer">undermine</span></li>
    <li>b. living together without marriage — <span class="answer">cohabitation</span></li>
    <li>c. a polite way of behaving — <span class="answer">courtesy</span></li>
    <li>d. a family of parents and children living together — <span class="answer">nuclear family</span></li>
    <li>e. the main or most important part of something — <span class="answer">cornerstone</span></li>
    <li>f. imagined something in the future — <span class="answer">envisaged</span></li>
    <li>g. the result of something — <span class="answer">outcome</span></li>
    <li>h. peaceful and friendly — <span class="answer">harmonious</span></li>
    <li>i. the chance of something happening — <span class="answer">probability</span></li>
    <li>j. a public disagreement or argument — <span class="answer">controversy</span></li>
